## üîí S√©curit√©

### Pratiques Impl√©ment√©es

#### 1. Application Security

- ‚úÖ **Helmet.js** - Headers HTTP s√©curis√©s
- ‚úÖ **Rate Limiting** - 100 req/15min par IP
- ‚úÖ **CORS** - Origins autoris√©es uniquement
- ‚úÖ **Input Validation** - Joi schemas
- ‚úÖ **API Keys** - Stock√©es en secrets K8s
- ‚úÖ **HTTPS/TLS 1.3** - Obligatoire en production

#### 2. Container Security

- ‚úÖ **Multi-stage builds** - Images minimales
- ‚úÖ **Non-root users** - UID 1001
- ‚úÖ **Read-only filesystem** - Sauf /tmp
- ‚úÖ **Security scanning** - Trivy daily
- ‚úÖ **Image signing** - Notary/Cosign
- ‚úÖ **No secrets in images** - Variables d'env

#### 3. Kubernetes Security

- ‚úÖ **RBAC** - Principe du moindre privil√®ge
- ‚úÖ **Network Policies** - Isolation pods
- ‚úÖ **Pod Security Standards** - Restricted
- ‚úÖ **Secrets encryption** - KMS
- ‚úÖ **Security contexts** - Capabilities dropped

#### 4. Infrastructure Security

- ‚úÖ **VPC isolation** - Subnets priv√©s/publics
- ‚úÖ **Security Groups** - Least privilege
- ‚úÖ **WAF** - Protection attaques web
- ‚úÖ **Secrets Manager** - AWS Secrets Manager
- ‚úÖ **Audit logs** - CloudTrail

### Scan de S√©curit√©

```bash
# Scan image Docker avec Trivy
trivy image transport-backend:latest

# Scan vuln√©rabilit√©s npm
npm audit

# Scan cluster Kubernetes
kubectl kube-bench

# Analyse code SonarQube
sonar-scanner
```

